      From everyone at RipplePop, thank you for using our services! Our goal has always been to provide you with the best work we can. We have grown quite a bit since our early days, and with our inability to know every one of our customers personally, we have to put in place some Terms of Service to help keep things clear for everyone.<br /><br />
 
When we say “Company”, “we”, “our”, or “us” in this document, we are referring to RipplePop LLC. When we say “contractor” in this document, we are referring to our internal RipplePop team members and contractors. When we say “you” in this document we are referring to you, the customer purchasing our Services. <br /><br />
 
When we say “Services”, we mean any product created and or maintained by RipplePop LLC. That includes all past RipplePop plans which may no longer be actively listed on our website. <br /><br />
 
When you use our Services, now or in the future, you are agreeing to the latest Terms of Service. That’s true for any of our existing and future products and all variations that we add to our Services over time. There may be times where we do not exercise or enforce any right or provision of the Terms of Service; in doing so, we are not waiving that right or position. These terms do contain a limitation for our liability. <br /><br />
 
If you violate any of the terms, we may terminate your account. We also reserve the right to terminate your account at any time and for any reason. That’s a broad statement and it means you need to place a lot of trust in us. We do our best to deserve that trust by being open about who we are, how we work, and always being open to your feedback. 
    </p>
