    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-900 graphik-bold mt-8">Payment, Refunds, and Plan Changes</p>
    <ol class="text-xl list-decimal ml-8 mt-4">
      <li>For paid Services that offer a free trial, we explain the length of the trial when you sign up. After that trial period, you need to pay by the completion of the trial to keep using the Service. If you do not pay, you will no longer have access to the Service until you make your payment. If you have utilized a trial in the past, you will not be eligible for a trial on the same Service offering again in the future.</li>
      <li>For paid Services, you will pay RipplePop at the rates set forth via our active pricing plans on our website. Payment is due upon registration for an account and will be billed for on a weekly basis. </li>
      <li>For paid Services that involve a daily hour cap for RipplePop contractors, any unused hours do not roll over and can not be utilized at a later date.</li>
      <li>For paid Services that involve a weekly hour cap for RipplePop contractors, you may not request more than 8 hours of work from your RipplePop contractor in a particular day. Any unused hours, that were purchased in bulk at the onset of the Service, do not carry over to the next month of the Service. From the day you register for your bulk hours, you have one month to use those hours before they expire. You will schedule the hours throughout the month with your RipplePop contractor. </li>
      <li>RipplePop contractor are presumed to be nonexempt from laws requiring premium pay for overtime, holiday work, or weekend work. RipplePop will charge the client special rates for premium work time only when a RipplePop contractor’s work on assignment to the client, viewed by itself, would legally require premium pay and the client has authorized, directed, or allowed the RipplePop contractor to work such premium work time. The client's special billing rate for premium hours will be a flat fee of $50 an hour for any overtime, holiday work, or weekend work that falls outside of the standard hours of the employment agreement.</li>
      <li>You have read and agree that you understand our <a href="/refunds" class="text-blue-500" target="_blank">Refund Policy</a> and how it may relate to your particular product choice.</li>
      <li>All RipplePop contractors are subject to RipplePop's standard USA holidays and days off assigned by RipplePop.</li>
      <li>If the client uses the services of any RipplePop contractor as its direct employee, as an independent contractor, or through any firm other than RipplePop during an active RipplePop plan or 365 days after cancellation of the RipplePop contractor to the client from RipplePop, the client must pay RipplePop a fee in the amount of the yearly RipplePop salary for that employee.</li>
      <li>If your payment is late or overdue, we will give you up to 3 business days of additional service while you finalize your payment. If your payment does not arrive within 3 business days of it being overdue, your plan will be paused and all work will halt until you have made your payment current.</li>
		<li>If you ever wish to change the plan you are on, you can contact us: <a href="mailto:hello@ripplepop.com" class="text-blue-500">hello@ripplepop.com</a>. Changes to your plan often involve a pro-ration of charges but can be handled on an individual basis depending on the scenario. You are allowed to upgrade/downgrade your service once per month with an active plan.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-900 graphik-bold mt-8">Non-Compete & Cooperation</p>
    <ul class="text-xl list-disc ml-8 mt-4">
      <li>RipplePop contractors are assigned to work for you. You can not under any circumstances, sell or staff RipplePop's contractors as if they were your own team members.</li>
      <li>RipplePop contractors are restricted from contacting any of your customers regarding any outside work other than what was assigned to the RipplePop contractor directly from you. This means, you will be the point of contact for the RipplePop contractor. If you want your RipplePop contractor replying directly to your customers, you may do that as long as the RipplePop contractor expresses their consent.</li>
      <li>RipplePop shall not solicit or contact any user, account, or related parties without your prior written consent. This means, if you are using RipplePop to get work done for clients you manage RipplePop will not and can not contact or approach your clients. Your clients are your clients, and we forbid RipplePop contractors from making contact with your clients without your explicit written consent to do so. If you want to connect us with a friend or someone who may be interested in our services, that is allowed.</li>
      <li>RipplePop can not claim any work that has been completed by the RipplePop contractor as our own. The work we complete for you under our Services is under your ownership and RipplePop claims not right to ownership of any of the Services rendered. This simply means you will not see us talking with anyone else about the work we have done for you, that work is confidential and RipplePop nor its contractors have ownership over the work rendered, you do. We may share your testimonial on our site if you permit us to.</li>
      <li>Both parties agree to cooperate fully and to provide assistance to the other part in the instance of an investigation and resolution of any complaints, claims, actions, or proceedings that may be brought by or that may involve RipplePop or its contractors. </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-900 graphik-bold mt-8">Extended Employment and Pay Raises</p>
    <ul class="text-xl list-disc ml-8 mt-4">
      <li>We have a lot of customers who stay with us for months on end, if not longer. If you are with us, and the same RipplePop contractor for 6 months or more, you can opt-in to giving your RipplePop contractor a raise. A raise equates to a $100/mo fee on top of your existing Service charge. This extra fee goes directly into the pocket of your RipplePop contractor and is a great way for you to reward a RipplePop contractor for their extended efforts with you. We can always work out a custom raise amount and we will contact you with regards to this raise after you have been with us for 6 months or more with the same active Service.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-900 graphik-bold mt-8">Swaps and Changes to Your Team</p>
    <ul class="text-xl list-disc ml-8 mt-4">
      <li>In order to swap in a new developer and replace your existing one, you must first cancel your plan with your existing developer. Then pick the replacement developer you wish to work with from our Developer List and you can begin on a new plan with them.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-2xl text-gray-900 graphik-bold mt-8">Liability</p>
    <p class="text-xl mt-4">
